In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed various topics. He expressed condolences for the victims of the recent terror attack in London and confirmed that the President is ready to provide consular assistance to any injured American citizens. Spicer also provided an update on the progress of the American Health Care Act, stating that the President is meeting with members of the House Freedom Caucus and the Tuesday Group to build support for the bill. He emphasized the need to repeal and replace Obamacare in order to drive down costs and increase access to healthcare. Spicer also mentioned that the President is continuing discussions with Republican House members and that the legislative affairs team has been in constant contact with them. He highlighted the amendments that have been incorporated into the bill to address concerns and improve the healthcare system. Additionally, Spicer mentioned that the President is looking forward to seeing Republicans fulfill their promise of repealing and replacing Obamacare. He also commented on the Senate Judiciary hearings for Judge Neil Gorsuch, expressing disappointment in Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer's announcement that Senate Democrats would be mounting a filibuster against Gorsuch's nomination. Spicer called on Schumer to abandon the attempt to block Gorsuch from receiving a fair up or down vote.